="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Author</FONT><B></TD><TD valign=top><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#000000>Comment</FONT><B></FONT></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#2f2f4f><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Registered User</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>9/14/00</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#5F9EA0>8:48:00 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=225.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Useful AC utility</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I can't remember if I've posted this before, but I've been running a program alongside AC lately called AC Location Tracker. <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/asherontracker/">www.geocities.com/asherontracker/</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
It's pretty nifty. It keeps track of your current location in AC and marks it on a detailed map of Dereth. You do have to Alt-Tab out of AC to view the map, and it doesn't work in dungeons yet, but it's still very handy.<br>
<br>
The best thing is, when you die, it marks the location of your corpse on the map, and even shows you the shortest route from your current location to your body. It also copies the coordinates of your body to the clipboard, so you can just Ctrl-v and paste the coords into the chat window to see them without leaving AC. There's been a couple of times when I died in the middle of nowhere, and never would have found my corpse without it.<br>
<br>
